/claim #649

Proposed-work issue: https://github.com/ramimbo/mergework/issues/677

Why this is useful:
- identifies a current scanner/API visibility gap: bounty rows expose award capacity but not advisory active-attempt summaries;
- proposes a bounded active-attempt count/warning plus the existing detailed attempt endpoint, so agents can notice overlapping work before coding;
- links live read-only API evidence from bounty id 96 and the separate attempts endpoint;
- reuses existing warning semantics and keeps attempts advisory only;
- includes concrete acceptance criteria, tests, duplicate search, and explicit non-goals;
- is distinct from #676 submission-mode routing, #672 proposed-work triage, #671/#673 pending payout visibility, #641 effective availability, and #645/#660 non-live PR reference checks.

No private data, credentials, wallet material, production mutation, price/exchange/bridge/off-ramp claims, or fabricated payout claims used.
